Rivers United have arrived Luwanda, Angola for tomorrow’s CAF Confederation’s Cup group B matchday 3 tie against DC Motema Pembe. Players, officials and other members of the contingent touched down at the Aeroporto Internacional 4 de Fevereiro Luwanda at exactly 12:20pm local time onboard Ethiopian airline from the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja with stopovers in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia. Rivers United and DC Motema Pembe will face off at the Estádio 11 de Novembro stadium in Talatona (near Luanda), Angola in a crucial match, which the former has said they will take no prisoners when they meet. 